003Cp>\u003Cimg src=\"/workPhotos/kat.JPG\" alt=\"image\">\u003C/p>",{"headings":100,"localImagePaths":103,"remoteImagePaths":104,"frontmatter":105,"imagePaths":107},[101],{"depth":19,"slug":102,"text":88},"we-cross-the-river",[],[],{"isDraft":21,"title":88,"snippet":16,"slug":85,"mainRole":91,"company":92,"category":89,"readingDuration":19,"pubDate":106,"coverAlt":14,"originalLink":20,"cover":93},"2025 5 31",[],"freshworks_ZulyInirio",{"id":108,"data":110,"body":114,"filePath":115,"digest":116,"rendered":117},{"coverAlt":14,"title":111,"slug":108,"snippet":16,"category":17,"pubDate":112,"readingDuration":19,"originalLink":44,"isDraft":21,"mainRole":17,"company":22,"cover":113},"Freshworks - Zuly Inirio - La Voz que Soy",["Date","2025-04-04T04:00:00.000Z"],"/workPhotos/fresh_zuly/zuly_004.avif","# Freshworks: Zuly Inirio - La Voz que Soy\n\nThis was my first Freshworks project at the Kellystrayhorn, it also helped that Zuly was kind and directed very officially. It was nice being able to work one on one with such a great vocalist and artist to bring their story to life.\n\n\n\u003Cdiv style=\"position: relative; width: 100%; height: 0; padding-bottom: 56.25%;\">\n  \u003Ciframe \n    src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/uQ8FDEyY86U?autoplay=1&mute=1&loop=1&playlist=uQ8FDEyY86U&controls=0&modestbranding=1&rel=0&showinfo=0&iv_load_policy=3&disablekb=1&fs=0&playsinline=1\" \n    title=\"YouTube video player\" \n    style=\"position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border: none;\"\n    allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" \n    allowfullscreen\n  >\u003C/iframe>\n\u003C/div>\n\n![image](/workPhotos/fresh_zuly/zuly_004.avif)\n\n![image](/workPhotos/fresh_zuly/zuly_001.avif)\n\n![image](/workPhotos/fresh_zuly/zuly_002.avif)\n\n![image](/workPhotos/fresh_zuly/zuly_005.avif)\n\n![image](/workPhotos/fresh_zuly/zuly_003.avif)\n\n*Photos by \u003Ca href=\"https://kelly-strayhorn.org\">Kelly-Strayhorn Theater\u003C/a>*","src/content/articles/25-4-4_Freshworks-ZulyInirio-LaVozqueSoy.md","151cd4b8cd8d6824",{"html":118,"metadata":119},"\u003Ch1 id=\"freshworks-zuly-inirio---la-voz-que-soy\">Freshworks: Zuly Inirio - La Voz que Soy\u003C/h1>\n\u003Cp>This was my first Freshworks project at the Kellystrayhorn, it also helped that Zuly was kind and directed very officially. It was nice being able to work one on one with such a great vocalist and artist to bring their story to life.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cdiv style=\"position: relative; width: 100%; height: 0; padding-bottom: 56.25%;\">\n  \u003Ciframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/uQ8FDEyY86U?autoplay=1&#x26;mute=1&#x26;loop=1&#x26;playlist=uQ8FDEyY86U&#x26;controls=0&#x26;modestbranding=1&#x26;rel=0&#x26;showinfo=0&#x26;iv_load_policy=3&#x26;disablekb=1&#x26;fs=0&#x26;playsinline=1\" title=\"YouTube video player\" style=\"position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border: none;\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen>\u003C/iframe>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cimg src=\"/workPhotos/fresh_zuly/zuly_004.avif\" alt=\"image\">\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cimg src=\"/workPhotos/fresh_zuly/zuly_001.avif\" alt=\"image\">\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cimg src=\"/workPhotos/fresh_zuly/zuly_002.avif\" alt=\"image\">\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cimg src=\"/workPhotos/fresh_zuly/zuly_005.avif\" alt=\"image\">\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cimg src=\"/workPhotos/fresh_zuly/zuly_003.avif\" alt=\"image\">\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cem>Photos by \u003Ca href=\"https://kelly-strayhorn.org\">Kelly-Strayhorn Theater\u003C/a>\u003C/em>\u003C/p>",{"headings":120,"localImagePaths":124,"remoteImagePaths":125,"frontmatter":126,"imagePaths":128},[121],{"depth":19,"slug":122,"text":123},"freshworks-zuly-inirio---la-voz-que-soy","Freshworks: Zuly Inirio - La Voz que Soy",[],[],{"isDraft":21,"title":111,"snippet":16,"slug":108,"mainRole":17,"company":22,"category":17,"readingDuration":19,"pubDate":127,"coverAlt":14,"originalLink":44,"cover":113},"2025 4 4",[],"lantern_night",{"id":129,"data":131,"body":139,"filePath":140,"digest":141,"rendered":142},{"coverAlt":132,"title":133,"slug":129,"snippet":134,"category":17,"pubDate":135,"readingDuration":19,"originalLink":136,"isDraft":21,"mainRole":17,"company":137,"cover":138},"friction is the feature cover","Pitt University Lantern Night","in a world where everything is free, nothing is valued.",["Date","2025-08-24T04:00:00.000Z"],"https://signull.substack.com/p/friction-is-the-feature","Fireside Events LLC","/workPhotos/Lantern_3.jpg","# University of Pittsburgh Lantern Night\nAt this point in my career, this was probably the most high level and high stress event I've worked, yet the challenge was perfect me in my development as an artist. The MagicQ MQ50 lighting console was something I had never worked with before, so I spent a lot of time in prep learning the ropes. \n\n![image](/workPhotos/Lantern_8.jpg)\n*Photos by \u003Ca href=\"https://www.claireemchmedia.com/portraits/\">Claire Emch\u003C/a>*\n\nFrom there, I worked with the \u003Ca href=\"https://www.fireside-events.com\">Fireside\u003C/a> team to build out the lighting rigs; we had a mix lights including Chauvet Maverick Storm 4 Profiles, Storm 2s, and Rogue Outcast Washes. We used the storms (as our highest output fixtures) to light an entire face of the Cathedral of Learning building and the Chapel on Pitt's Campus; at night during the event this created an amazing effect. The washes and other assorted fixtures were used as front and back light for the podium on the stage, however the most complex lighting element wasn't even done yet.\n\n![image](/workPhotos/Lantern_4.jpg)\n\nI had the pleasure of working with the team at \u003Ca href=\"https://www.crowdsynctechnology.com\">Crowdsync\u003C/a> to use their custom bracelet wireless LED system, which has been used by artists like Kygo, organizing like iHeartradio, and in football stadiums across the US. We used these as the lanterns the entire audience of 3,000 plus persons would be holding during the show. I used their DMX node to control thousands of grouped LEDs for the biggest moment of the night; the passing of the lanterns from faculty to the first year students of the university. \n\n![image](/workPhotos/Lantern_9.JPG)\n\nThis moment of the night required that all the lights I've mentioned transition from blue to gold. A simple thing in theory but took the work of myself and the entire Fireside team to pull off successfully. The night of the event had a few bumps in the road but with a little quick thinking and the support of the team around me we got it done. The entire crowd cheered and we knew we'd made these freshman's college experience great. What a great night this was, and what a fabulous experience.\n\n![image](/workPhotos/Lantern_10.JPG)\n\n![image](/workPhotos/Lantern_3.jpg)\n\n![image](/workPhotos/Lantern_5.jpg)\n\n![image](/workPhotos/Lantern_6.jpg)\n\n![image](/workPhotos/Lantern_2.webp)\n*Paperwork by Liam Lyons IV*","src/content/articles/25-8-24_PittUniversityLanternNight.md","57556101277e0d52",{"html":143,"metadata":144},"\u003Ch1 id=\"university-of-pittsburgh-lantern-night\">University of Pittsburgh Lantern Night\u003C/h1>\n\u003Cp>At this point in my career, this was probably the most high level and high stress event I’ve worked, yet the challenge was perfect me in my development as an artist. The MagicQ MQ50 lighting console was something I had never worked with before, so I spent a lot of time in prep learning the ropes.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cimg src=\"/workPhotos/Lantern_8.jpg\" alt=\"image\">\n\u003Cem>Photos by \u003Ca href=\"https://www.claireemchmedia.com/portraits/\">Claire Emch\u003C/a>\u003C/em>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>From there, I worked with the \u003Ca href=\"https://www.fireside-events.com\">Fireside\u003C/a> team to build out the lighting rigs; we had a mix lights including Chauvet Maverick Storm 4 Profiles, Storm 2s, and Rogue Outcast Washes. We used the storms (as our highest output fixtures) to light an entire face of the Cathedral of Learning building and the Chapel on Pitt’s Campus; at night during the event this created an amazing effect. The washes and other assorted fixtures were used as front and back light for the podium on the stage, however the most complex lighting element wasn’t even done yet.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cimg src=\"/workPhotos/Lantern_4.jpg\" alt=\"image\">\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>I had the pleasure of working with the team at \u003Ca href=\"https://www.crowdsynctechnology.com\">Crowdsync\u003C/a> to use their custom bracelet wireless LED system, which has been used by artists like Kygo, organizing like iHeartradio, and in football stadiums across the US. We used these as the lanterns the entire audience of 3,000 plus persons would be holding during the show. I used their DMX node to control thousands of grouped LEDs for the biggest moment of the night; the passing of the lanterns from faculty to the first year students of the university.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cimg src=\"/workPhotos/Lantern_9.JPG\" alt=\"image\">\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>This moment of the night required that all the lights I’ve mentioned transition from blue to gold. A simple thing in theory but took the work of myself and the entire Fireside team to pull off successfully. The night of the event had a few bumps in the road but with a little quick thinking and the support of the team around me we got it done. The entire crowd cheered and we knew we’d made these freshman’s college experience great. What a great night this was, and what a fabulous experience.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cimg src=\"/workPhotos/Lantern_10.JPG\" alt=\"image\">\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cimg src=\"/workPhotos/Lantern_3.jpg\" alt=\"image\">\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cimg src=\"/workPhotos/Lantern_5.jpg\" alt=\"image\">\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cimg src=\"/workPhotos/Lantern_6.jpg\" alt=\"image\">\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cimg src=\"/workPhotos/Lantern_2.webp\" alt=\"image\">\n\u003Cem>Paperwork by Liam Lyons IV\u003C/em>\u003C/p>",{"headings":145,"localImagePaths":149,"remoteImagePaths":150,"frontmatter":151,"imagePaths":153},[146],{"depth":19,"slug":147,"text":148},"university-of-pittsburgh-lantern-night","University of Pittsburgh Lantern Night",[],[],{"isDraft":21,"title":133,"snippet":134,"slug":129,"mainRole":17,"company":137,"category":17,"readingDuration":19,"pubDate":152,"coverAlt":132,"originalLink":136,"cover":138},"2025 8 24",[],"TheChallengerProjectMusicVideos",{"id":154,"data":156,"body":162,"filePath":163,"digest":164,"rendered":165},{"coverAlt":14,"title":157,"slug":154,"snippet":16,"category":158,"pubDate":159,"readingDuration":19,"originalLink":44,"isDraft":21,"mainRole":158,"company":160,"cover":161},"The Challenger Project Music Videos","Videography",["Date","2025-08-08T04:00:00.000Z"],"LyonsIV","/workPhotos/TPC_bandphotos_edits_005.jpg","# The Challenger Project Music Videos\n\n\u003Cdiv style=\"position: relative; width: 100%; height: 0; padding-bottom: 56.25%;\">\n  \u003Ciframe \n    src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/te5oH0nPSrM?autoplay=1&mute=1&loop=1&playlist=te5oH0nPSrM&modestbranding=1&rel=0&iv_load_policy=3&disablekb=1&fs=0&playsinline=1\" \n    title=\"YouTube video player\" \n    style=\"position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border: none;\"\n    allow=\"accelerometer; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" \n    allowfullscreen\n  >\u003C/iframe>\n\u003C/div>\n\n![image](/workPhotos/TPC_bandphotos_edits_005.jpg)","src/content/articles/25-8-8_TCPMusicVideo.md","66e1753d19893ae8",{"html":166,"metadata":167},"\u003Ch1 id=\"the-challenger-project-music-videos\">The Challenger Project Music Videos\u003C/h1>\n\u003Cdiv style=\"position: relative; width: 100%; height: 0; padding-bottom: 56.25%;\">\n  \u003Ciframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/te5oH0nPSrM?autoplay=1&#x26;mute=1&#x26;loop=1&#x26;pl